 inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Guillaume de Croy was born in 1190, his father, Marc Arpad de Hongrie, was 32 and his mother, Catherine de Croÿ, was 40. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Anne-Cécile De Guînes. He died about 1224, in Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1190–Abt 1224":"1190–umbes 1224","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1180–1214":"1180–1214","1185–1214":"1185–1214","1190–1224":"1190–1224","1198–1245":"1198–1245","1215–1267":"1215–1267","1263–1313":"1263–1313","1158–1191":"1158–1191","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1190":"1190","1198":"1198","1263":"1263","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","Abt 1224":"umbes 1224","environ 1191":"umbes 1191","1150":"1150","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1313":"1313","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1224":"1224","1267":"1267","1245":"1245","about 1215":"umbes 1215","Airaines, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Airaines, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Airaines, Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1190–Abt 1224":"1190–noin 1224","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1180–1214":"1180–1214","1185–1214":"1185–1214","1190–1224":"1190–1224","1198–1245":"1198–1245","1215–1267":"1215–1267","1263–1313":"1263–1313","1158–1191":"1158–1191","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1198":"1198","1263":"1263","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","Abt 1224":"noin 1224","environ 1191":"noin 1191","1150":"1150","1191":"1191","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1313":"1313","1214":"1214","1158":"1158","1224":"1224","1267":"1267","1245":"1245","about 1215":"noin 1215",